Run with:


pytest tests/test_vault_lint.py -v --cov=.openspec-cli/lib/vault_lint --cov-fail-under=90
Acceptance Criteria
 os-vault-lint contracts/ exits 0 on the existing savings_product.py
 os-vault-lint exits 1 and prints FILE:LINE [RULE] message for each violation
 os-vault-test runs os-vault-lint first and aborts (exit 1) if lint fails
 CI vault-lint step runs before pytest and fails the build on any violation
 pytest tests/test_vault_lint.py --cov-fail-under=90 passes
 ruff check .openspec-cli/lib/vault_lint.py passes (no lint errors in the linter itself)
 mypy .openspec-cli/lib/vault_lint.py --strict passes
Non-Functional Requirements
Performance: lint must complete in under 2 seconds for a directory of ≤20 contracts
No runtime dependencies: vault_lint.py uses only Python standard library (ast, sys, pathlib, argparse) — no pip install required
Deterministic output: violations are reported in file-then-line order; CI output is reproducible
No false negatives on existing violations: the linter must catch all patterns listed in the FORBIDDEN section of vault-smart-contracts.md
Branch: feature/KAN-7-backend
Commit convention: feat(vault-lint): add os-vault-lint for sandbox restriction validation
